00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:05.679
as we think about the timing and timeline

00:00:05.679 --> 00:00:07.039
of what we're celebrating.

00:00:07.039 --> 00:00:10.000
Of course, next Sunday, Resurrection Sunday.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.560
And every single Sunday we meet on Sunday

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:16.059
because we serve a risen savior.

00:00:16.059 --> 00:00:19.700
And once in the year we celebrate specifically

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:22.219
Resurrection Sunday, Easter Sunday.

00:00:22.219 --> 00:00:24.760
And I'm thankful even as I prayed this morning

00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:28.319
that he rose again according to the scriptures, amen.

00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:31.959
And what a blessing, the Old Testament prophesied of it.

00:00:31.959 --> 00:00:35.240
The New Testament in the gospels, Jesus spoke of it.

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:38.560
Destroy this temple and in three days I will raise it up.

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:42.439
And hallelujah, the grave could not hold him.

00:00:42.439 --> 00:00:44.759
