00:00:50.479 --> 00:00:52.520
And of course, this week being the week

00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:56.200
in which we would commemorate the fact that Jesus died

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:00.200
on the cross of Calvary for the sin of humanity.

00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:03.360
And I'll be in Hebrews chapter number 10 this morning.

00:01:03.360 --> 00:01:07.360
And in fact, as you begin to look at Hebrews chapter number 10

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:09.919
the Bible makes a comparison there

00:01:09.919 --> 00:01:12.760
between the Old Testament, the law,

00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:16.000
having a shadow of good things to come.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:18.160
And I'm gonna read some, actually I'm gonna ask you

00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:21.180
to take your hymnal as well and look at a song real quickly

00:01:21.180 --> 00:01:23.440
to kind of begin our service.

00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:26.199
But there's a verse that I wanna point out

00:01:26.199 --> 00:01:29.199
