00:04:08.059 --> 00:04:11.100
It goes through and it talks about angels and Moses

00:04:11.100 --> 00:04:13.779
and the law and all sorts of things

00:04:13.779 --> 00:04:15.940
and we find that in every example

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:18.059
that is provided in the book of Hebrews

00:04:18.059 --> 00:04:21.459
that Christ is superior, he's greater.

00:04:21.459 --> 00:04:24.260
We understand that he's God in flesh.

00:04:24.260 --> 00:04:28.859
What a blessing to know that Jesus, the Lamb of God,

00:04:28.859 --> 00:04:30.779
left the throne room of heaven

00:04:30.779 --> 00:04:32.700
to come to the sin-cursed world.

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:37.059
Yes, he was born in a manger, but he was born to die

00:04:37.059 --> 00:04:41.579
and we understand that as we get into the book of Hebrews,

00:04:41.579 --> 00:04:43.660
you come to the 10th chapter

00:04:44.540 --> 00:04:46.459
and the writer of Hebrews begins to explain

00:04:46.459 --> 00:04:48.940
the deficiencies of the law

00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:51.540
and the Old Testament sacrificial system.

00:04:51.540 --> 00:04:53.519
Now understand that this was the law,

00:04:53.519 --> 00:04:55.100
this was the sacrificial system

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:58.940
that was given by God to his people,

00:04:58.940 --> 00:05:02.359
but the law and the sacrificial system was deficient.

00:05:02.359 --> 00:05:05.820
It was a shadow of good things to come.

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:08.179
We find that the writer of the book of Galatians,

00:05:08.179 --> 00:05:09.779
the apostle Paul, under the inspiration

00:05:09.779 --> 00:05:12.820
