00:05:12.820 --> 00:05:14.540
in verse 21 and 22,

00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:17.420
is the law then against the promises of God?

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:21.459
God forbid, for if there had been a law given,

00:05:21.459 --> 00:05:23.959
which could have given life,

00:05:23.959 --> 00:05:28.540
verily righteousness should have been by the law,

00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:32.579
but the scripture hath concluded all under sin

00:05:32.579 --> 00:05:35.600
that the promise of faith of Jesus Christ

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:39.739
might be given to them that believe.

00:05:39.739 --> 00:05:41.299
The law cannot save.

00:05:41.299 --> 00:05:43.739
In fact, the law simply condemns.

00:05:43.739 --> 00:05:47.459
The law simply reveals that we're sinners.

00:05:47.459 --> 00:05:49.940
What the law does, it cannot save us,

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:51.339
it cannot give us life,

00:05:51.339 --> 00:05:54.859
but the law will bring us to the only one,

00:05:54.859 --> 00:05:58.540
the Lord Jesus Christ, that can give life.

00:05:58.540 --> 00:06:00.820
And we find that here,

00:06:00.820 --> 00:06:03.420
as you move through Hebrews chapter number 10,

00:06:03.420 --> 00:06:06.700
he speaks about the deficiencies of the law

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:09.100
and the Old Testament sacrificial system,

00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:11.059
but then as you move through the chapter,

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:16.100
you read about the sufficiency of Christ's atonement

00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:17.660
on the cross of Calvary.

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:20.380
We understand that it's a substitutionary atonement.

00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:22.779
He died for me.

00:06:22.779 --> 00:06:25.059
And it's important that every single person

00:06:25.059 --> 00:06:28.500
on planet Earth recognizes and understands

00:06:28.500 --> 00:06:30.140
that for me, he died.

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:33.380
He loved me personally, and he died for me.

00:06:33.380 --> 00:06:35.660
It was a substitutionary atonement.

00:06:35.660 --> 00:06:38.700
And we see as you continue through the book,

00:06:38.700 --> 00:06:40.260
or through the 10th chapter,

00:06:40.260 --> 00:06:44.220
that you start getting into even the impact of that

00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:46.260
on believers.

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:48.700
See, the old system, as it says in verse number one,

00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.899
notice in Hebrews 10 and verse number one,

00:06:50.899 --> 00:06:53.260
for the law, again, that old system,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:57.179
having a shadow of good things to come

00:06:57.179 --> 00:07:01.220
and not the very image of the things

00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:04.739
can never, with those sacrifices

00:07:04.739 --> 00:07:08.339
which they offered year by year continually,

00:07:08.380 --> 00:07:12.100
make the comers thereunto perfect.

00:07:12.100 --> 00:07:14.980
He says in verse two, for then would they not

00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:17.140
