00:12:41.900 --> 00:12:46.500
No, it's that he that is just, Jesus,

00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:50.059
died for the unjust, for us.

00:12:50.059 --> 00:12:54.199
It's that as we read in 2 Corinthians 5 in verse number 20,

00:12:54.199 --> 00:12:58.559
for he hath made him to be sin for us,

00:12:58.559 --> 00:13:02.139
who knew no sin that we might be made

00:13:02.139 --> 00:13:05.559
the righteousness of God in him.

00:13:05.559 --> 00:13:08.080
And so this morning, as we begin to think about this idea

00:13:08.080 --> 00:13:11.680
of remission and this plan that God has for us

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:15.119
and we see it outlined here again, the Old Testament,

00:13:15.119 --> 00:13:19.479
the Bible uses that term, a shadow of good things to come

